****************************************************************************
* README *******************************************************************
****************************************************************************
Fréchet tools: Java utilities for visualizing the Fréchet distance.
****************************************************************************
This program is a set of GUI components that may be used to visualize the 
so called Fréchet distance. To launch the individual components, the scripts
located within the 'scripts' directory on the top level of the project 
hierarchy may be used. Here's a short explanation:


scripts/frechet: ***********************************************************
****************************************************************************
launch java with the classpath defined correctly. This is not a specific
application launcher but it may be used to start any class within the
classpath.

scripts/line.editor.sh: ****************************************************
****************************************************************************
launch the line editor. This is a test for the line-editing component for
single line segments.

scripts/freespace.single.sh: ***********************************************
****************************************************************************
launch the program that shows two line segment editors along with a single
cell Fréchet diagram representing the free space created by the line
segments.

scripts/freespace.curve.sh: ************************************************
****************************************************************************
launch the program that allows the user to define two polygonal chains and
then offers a few utility functions to operate on those lines. Most 
importantly the user may display a Fréchet diagram that is connected to
the two first lines of the line editor.
